      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "THE GLEN (3) won two back over the 1400m at Goulburn before tiring out of contention when setting the tempo over 1500m journey most recently. McDougall remains in the saddle and he rates highly on those recent efforts. Should be prominent in the run and prove tough to peg back INITIATE (1) was far too good over this course and distance, scoring by 1.9L under similar circumstances. The draw may be an issue, but she does have good early speed and Owen remains in the saddle. Can go on with the job without surprising. MR USHER (4) settled last but rounded them up at the Sapphire Coast a couple of weeks ago on a day where it was hard to make ground. Well placed here on the back of that effort and can repeat the dose. ONE MORE BOUT (2) is third-up now and gets the blinkers back on. Can feature. SOLICITING (6) is first-up here but can turn in a strong performance on her home deck.",
